{center}
{subhead}Amiga Active goes Digital{def}
{left}
{pp}
From November, Amiga Active, the leading Amiga magazine will be changing its focus
towards the AmigaDE, where the Amiga's future is now heading and will change its name
to 'digital'.
{pp}
The magazine will focus on leading technology in distributed computing, the internet,
wireless and digital media.
{pp}
Digital will be released on November 29th and will cost £3.50 per issue, there will no
no cover mounted CD-ROM any more and Amiga coverage will be replaced with a broader
coverage of new technology. The magazine will cover news, reviews, features and regular
sections as before.
{pp}